self.zeroSemaphore.release() # 19
# 20

for i in range(1, self.n + 1, 2): # 22
self.oddSemaphore.acquire() # 23
printNumber(i) # 24
self.zeroSemaphore.release() # 25

class Solution: # 1
def crawl(self, startUrl: str, htmlParser: 'HtmlParser') -> List[str]: # 2
hostname = urlparse(startUrl).hostname # 3
seen = set([startUrl]) # 4
lock = Lock() # 5
unseen = Queue() # 6
unseen.put(startUrl) # 7
# 8
def worker(): # 9
while True: # 10
url = unseen.get() # 11
if url is None: # 12
break # 13
# 14
# 15
for next_url in htmlParser.getUrls(url): # 16
# 17
if urlparse(next_url).hostname == hostname: # 18
with lock: # 19
if next_url not in seen: # 20
seen.add(next_url) # 21
unseen.put(next_url) # 22
# 23
unseen.task_done() # 24
# 25
threads = [] # 26
num_threads = 10 # 27
# 28
# 29
for _ in range(num_threads): # 30
thread = Thread(target=worker) # 31
thread.daemon = True # 32
thread.start() # 33
# 34
threads.append(thread) # 35
# 36
# 37
unseen.join() # 38
# 39
# 40
for _ in range(num_threads): # 41
unseen.put(None) # 42
# 43
# 44
for thread in threads: # 45
thread.join() # 46
# 47

# 9

# 11

return self.values[i] # 13
# 14

# 16
with self.locks[src], self.locks[dst]: # 17
amount = min(amount, self.values[src]) # 18

self.values[dst] += amount # 20
# 21
def snapshot(self): # 22
# 23

for i in range(self.nbuckets): # 25
with self.locks[i]: # 26
snapshot.append(self.values[i]) # 27
return snapshot # 28
# 29

nbuckets = buckets.nbuckets # 31

src = random.randrange(nbuckets) # 33
dst = random.randrange(nbuckets) # 34
if dst != src: # 35
amount = random.randrange(20) # 36
